        {
          "type": "note",
          "id": "zn0089",
          "layoutPosition": "absolute",
          "x": 8540,
          "y": 930,
          "name": "note",
          "width": 1440,
          "height": 130,
          "content": "FRAME 7 \u2014 COLLAPSED + DRILLED (Knowledge Base). Two bug fixes + one UX decision. (1) The drilled context band drops the 'Soleur' wordmark AND the theme toggle (bug #1: they must NOT appear in drilled states); only icons remain \u2014 back chevron, gold org avatar, repo dot, section icon (book-open). (2) Identity icons never unmount (TR1 / ADR-047). (3) DECISION \u2014 at 56px the KB file tree CANNOT collapse to icons (folders vs files are indistinguishable as bare glyphs, and indent-only loses the hierarchy). Of {a: force-expand whole rail, b: icon/indent-only tree, c: auto-expand a peek panel}, we RECOMMEND (c): drilling auto-expands a 200px tree-peek panel anchored to the 56px icon spine. The spine stays collapsed (identity + reclaimed chrome width preserved); the collapse chevron becomes a PIN \u2014 unpin to dismiss the peek back to the spine. This keeps the reclaimed real-estate win while making the tree legible, and avoids option (a)'s jarring full re-expand and option (b)'s unreadable glyph soup."
        }
      ]
    }
